in the ground.. well it moves.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHuh, must be for big objects like bases\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vv3k70r","CreatedById":208078,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-23T07:41:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223896701\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198901\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221608507323\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201607\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Miguelsgamingch\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/21/2020 at 12:35 AM, Miguelsgamingch said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd yeah, the construction lamp is moving.. by its own..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMobile site lamp - its a feature \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EIts annoying with all this experiment units too - they just walk, roll, get up again...\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223896741\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198901\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221608511311\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201607\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Miguelsgamingch\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/21/2020 at 1:41 AM, Miguelsgamingch said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope, When I Plant a flag it thens drops. like a flop.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMeybe area is already claimed by someone else?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike The Mighty Kraken?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou cant claim his space just like that - You have to beat him.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StopIteration","CreatedById":208942,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-23T10:12:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIIRC from when I was playing around with this earlier, it depends how you place them.\u00A0 If you place them with construction mode using an engineer, they roll all over the place.\u00A0 But if you place them using the arrow button from the inventory, they will stay put.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have no idea why there are two different modes for placing these deployables, each with totally different results.\u00A0 You can\u0027t attach them to any thing or place them in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E, so construction mode doesn\u0027t even make sense for them (and of course can only be done by an engineer, which is weird for deployables).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-23T11:10:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223898082\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198901\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221608718377\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208942\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StopIteration\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n57 minutes ago, StopIteration said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have no idea why there are two different modes for placing these deployables, each with totally different results.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause with the deploy icon (down pointing arrow) you\u0027re telling them to deploy it. Going into construction mode and dropping it, you\u0027re telling them to drop it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-12-23T11:10:43Z\u0022 title=\u002212/23/2020 11:10  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 23, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Superfluous J\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StopIteration","CreatedById":208942,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-23T11:49:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223898092\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198901\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221608721825\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n43 minutes ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou\u0027re telling them to drop it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah and it\u0027s bad design because I think a lot of people (such as \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, and I think I saw Matt Lowne do it too in his video) \u0022deploy\u0022 things using construction mode, and also it is weird that only engineers are skilled enough to be capable of dropping things (but anyone can deploy them).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-12-23T11:54:49Z\u0022 title=\u002212/23/2020 11:54  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 23, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by StopIteration\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Eclarification\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-23T12:43:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223898101\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198901\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221608724175\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208942\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StopIteration\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n52 minutes ago, StopIteration said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah and it\u0027s bad design because I think a lot of people (such as \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, and I think I saw Matt Lowne do it too in his video) \u0022deploy\u0022 things using construction mode, and also it is weird that only engineers are skilled enough to be capable of dropping things (but anyone can deploy them).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWeird doesn\u2019t mean unrealistic. Could be union regulations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}